<h1>Learn More</h1>
<div class="initiative-underline"></div>
<p><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">Beginning <b><u>September 3, 2025,</u></b>&nbsp;the Walk In Permitting Center will be open every Wednesday from 8:30 am to 10:30 am.</span>&nbsp;<u1:p></u1:p></p>
<p>Are you a homeowner, homeowner's contractor, or homeowner's agent (excluding Professional Expeditors) with questions regarding minor residential projects?</p>
<p>Mayor Caroline Simmons and City staff are offering dedicated hours where constituents can walk in and ask questions regarding residential and minor commercial projects such as food businesses, cosmetology, barber, and retail food establishments. Let us help you navigate the permitting or license process. These hours are designed specifically for those who are seeking to open a business, complete an alteration or addition, legalize work done without permits to their residential or small commercial projects, or add an ADU to their single-family property. This time is not for plan review or permit issuance but to answer questions and offer guidance.</p>
<div class="schedule-info">
<p><strong>Hours: 8:30 am to 10:30 am</strong></p>
<p><strong>Dates:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>September 3, 2025</li>
    <li>September 9, 2025</li>
    <li>September 17, 2025</li>
    <li>September 24, 2025</li>
    <li>October 1, 2025</li>
    <li>October 8, 2025</li>
    <li>October 15, 2025</li>
    <li>October 22, 2025</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Location:</strong> Stamford Government Center, 7th Floor Lobby</p>
</div>
